description: The Odisha government downgraded former CM Naveen Patnaik's security from Z to Y category, withdrawing most of his security personnel. Following a high-level committee's recommendation, Patnaik is to be assigned two constables of havildar rank, with additional security provided as needed, including during out-of-state tours.
title: Odisha downgrades Naveen Patnaik security from Z to Y

description: B R Naidu, the new chairman of Tirumala Tirupati Devasthanam (TTD) Board, emphasizes that all employees at Tirumala, the sacred site in Andhra Pradesh, should be Hindus. He plans to discuss staff reassignment or voluntary retirement for those of other religions with the state government. Naidu commits to addressing irregularities and maintaining temple sanctity.
title: All working in Tirumala must be Hindus: New temple trust head

description: For many years, the villagers of Sammoo in Himachal Pradesh have refrained from celebrating Diwali due to a curse from a woman who committed Sati on Diwali. Fearing misfortune and disaster, residents continue to observe the tragic event by staying indoors and avoiding festivities.
title: 'Cursed' by sati, Himachal village keeps off Diwali

description: Scammers are targeting individuals by posing as law enforcement officials through video calls, falsely accusing them of serious crimes and demanding money to resolve the charges. Using fabricated warrants and pressure tactics, victims, including elderly individuals, have been coerced into transferring large sums, with incidents reported in Hyderabad involving losses of up to Rs 5.9 crore.
title: 'Digital arrest': How cyber crooks use fear to loot victims

description: Many villages in Maharashtra have celebrated Diwali without firecrackers for over a decade to reduce air and noise pollution. Villages like Borade, Manyachiwadi, Langarpeth, and Padali have adopted this practice, with the Satara Zilla Parishad encouraging cracker-free celebrations. Violators face fines, and alternative events like lighting diyas and games are organized.
title: Maharashtra villages spark change with no-cracker Diwali

description: Over the past five years, many of the 27 outgoing state cabinet ministers in Mumbai experienced a moderate rise in their financial status, primarily due to land and flat acquisitions. However, significant increases were seen by Aditi Tatkare with a 772% rise, Ravindra Chavan with a 117% increase, and Sanjay Rathod logging a 220% growth.
title: Assets of ministers Aditi Tatkare, Sanjay Rathod and CM soar in 5 years

description: CBI has arrested two IRS officers, Deepak Kumar Sharma and Rahul Kumar, along with three CGST superintendents for bribery. They detained a businessman for 18 hours, demanding Rs 60 lakh to settle a pharma issue. After initial payment, the businessman was released but approached CBI, leading to arrests after a sting operation.
title: 2 IRS officers, 3 CGST superintendents held in `50 lakh bribery case

description: Maharashtra Ekikaran Samiti (MES) plans a 'black day' rally to coincide with Kannada Rajyotsava, despite legal and police pushback. The rally protests the inclusion of Belagavi in Karnataka and rallies Marathi-speaking people. Security is heightened, and unauthorized rallies will face legal action.
title: Tensions rise in Belagavi as pro-Maha outfit set for 'black day' rally today

description: Jammu and Kashmir now operates as a Union Territory, an accepted reality, according to Lt Governor Manoj Sinha. Celebrating the status, despite boycott by local parties and criticism from PDP's Mehbooba Mufti and NC leader Omar Abdullah, Sinha assured that statehood will be eventually restored. Promises include investments of Rs 1 lakh crore and creation of 5 lakh jobs.
title: J&K CM Omar skips UT day, LG slams ‘dual character’

description: PM Modi, at Rashtriya Ekta Diwas, emphasized national unity and a uniform civil code while warning against 'urban Naxals' seeking to destabilize India. He highlighted efforts by internal and external forces to tarnish India's growing global reputation. Modi's comments come after UP CM Yogi Adityanath's statement on unity endorsed by the RSS.
title: Ahead of Maharashtra polls, PM Modi talks of UCC, 'ek hain toh safe hain'

description: The rupee closed near an all-time low against the dollar, ending at 84.08, with RBI intervention keeping it steady amid US election anxiety. The rupee dipped 0.3% in October, trading between 83.79 and 84.1. With potential Trump win, RBI prepped for sudden outflows, though importers and exporters may overlook rising global risks.
title: Rupee ends October near record low amid outflows

description: Swiggy has received enthusiastic investor interest for its $1.4-billion IPO in India, with bids from big investors like Norges Bank and Fidelity exceeding $15 billion. The IPO, launching next week, has seen its valuation reduced to $11.3 billion due to a recent market correction.
title: Swiggy IPO gets $15 billion bids from Norway's wealth fund, fidelity

description: The stock market ended Samvat year 2080 on a negative note, but despite this, investors' wealth in India surged to Rs 453 lakh crore, marking the year as the biggest wealth-creating period. Contributing factors included a stable government, strong macroeconomic fundamentals, and significant domestic fund inflows.
title: Investors become richer by $1.5 trillion since last Diwali

description: The US has imposed sanctions on nearly 400 entities and individuals from over a dozen countries, including India and China, for allegedly supplying Russia with advanced technology to support its military activities in Ukraine. The sanctions target organizations in Russia, UAE, Turkey, Thailand, Malaysia, and Switzerland, aiming to disrupt critical technology flow to Russia's defense sector.
title: US sanctions 400 entities, including Indian firms, for tech supplies to Russia

description: Senior BJP leader and MLA from Nagrota, Devender Singh Rana, passes away in Faridabad. Rana, Jitendra Singh's younger brother, was a prominent figure in J&K politics and a strong advocate for the Dogra community. His sudden demise leaves behind his family and has shocked his supporters and colleagues.
title: BJP MLA Devender Singh Rana passes away

description: TPG Nambiar, the visionary founder of BPL and a pioneer in India’s consumer electronics industry, passed away at the age of 95. He established BPL in 1963 and led the company to prominence in the 1980s with high-quality electronic products. Despite its decline in the early 2000s, BPL left a lasting impact in the electronics sector.
title: BPL founder TPG Nambiar passes away

description: Former President Donald Trump criticized current US leadership for ignoring violence against Hindus and other minorities in Bangladesh, stating such incidents wouldn't have happened during his term. He promises to protect Hindu Americans and strengthen US-India relations if re-elected, emphasizing a focus on freedom and economic growth.
title: Trump condemns violence against Hindus in Bangladesh

description: India's urban middle class is cutting back on spending due to inflation and unemployment, revealing weakness in urban demand for the second consecutive quarter. Major companies like Hindustan Unilever and Reliance's retail unit have reported softer consumption, impacting their earnings and the broader economic outlook.
title: Are India's consumption hiccups signalling stress?

description: Horoscope Today: Read daily horoscope predictions for November 1, 2024. Know all about the astrological events and influences that will be affecting each of the 12 zodiac signs. Get ready to discover what the stars have in store for you today.
title: Horoscope Today: Read your today's astrological predictions

description: With the U.S. elections approaching, concerns about voting fraud and partisan rulings heighten tensions. A Pennsylvania TV station mistakenly aired test run results showing Kamala Harris winning, sparking conspiracy theories. Early voting sees confrontations, reflecting the deeply polarized environment, as notable incidents include a Supreme Court ruling on voter roll purging and worries over hidden votes within households.
title: Americans brace for gridlock amid talk of voter fraud and stolen election

description: This Diwali, consumer spending on snacks and gifts soared despite inflation concerns. Companies like Naturals Ice Cream, Dabur, and Parle Products saw significant sales boosts through affordable gift packs and strategic pricing. Urban areas showed budget caution, while rural demand remained steady. Further festive purchases are expected to maintain momentum.
title: Inflation fails to dampen Diwali snacking as gifts pack a punch

description: The longstanding practice of political betting persists, with both potential manipulation and its impact on perceptions concerning. Legal debates are ongoing over regulating such markets in the US. Social trust in crowd wisdom and economic stakes make these markets influential but potentially risky without strict oversight, as reflected in past financial market behaviors and Brexit betting outcomes.
title: 'Wisdom of crowds': Could political betting swing the US election?

description: McDonald's recalls raw onions from its menu following an E. coli outbreak that affected 90 people across 13 states, resulting in one death and 27 hospitalizations. The FDA traced the contamination to Taylor Farms. McDonald's temporarily halted the sale of Quarter Pounders in response to the outbreak.
title: McDonald's E. coli outbreak: US health officials blame onions as cases rise to 90

description: Congress demands the Election Commission of India to remove Maharashtra DGP Rashmi Shukla for alleged bias and escalating political violence against opposition during the upcoming assembly elections, highlighting her past controversy involving illegal phone tapping while serving in other police capacities.
title: Cong seeks removal of Maha DGP over alleged 'bias' against opposition

description: President Joe Biden's comment referring to Trump supporters as 'garbage' sparked a wave of denigration, with Trump donning a sanitation worker's uniform to mock Democrats. White House reassures Biden's statement was misinterpreted, not aimed at all Trump supporters. Kamala Harris distances herself from the remark, emphasizing respect for voters' choices.
title: Bin there done that: MAGA and Dems throw garbage at each other

description: In a notable development, Heinrich Klaasen surpassed Virat Kohli by securing the top retention price of Rs 23 crore for IPL 2025. Sunrisers Hyderabad emphasized Klaasen's significant impact, while Kohli and Nicholas Pooran were retained for Rs 21 crore each by RCB and LSG respectively on Thursday. This highlights the franchises' confidence in their key players.

description: Ahead of the November 20 assembly elections, major political parties in Maharashtra face challenges from Independent candidates with identical names, which may confuse voters. In the Sangli district, Rohit Raosaheb Patil competes against three other Independents with similar names. In Pune, candidates Bapusaheb Tukaram Pathare and Ashwini Nitin Kadam also encounter opponents with almost identical names.

description: Diwali, celebrated on October 31, 2024, marks Lord Ram’s return home, with festivities featuring diyas, lights, and crackers. The Lakshmi puja muhurat is from 07:19 PM to 9:11 PM. title: Top Diwali wishes: Send warm messages, wishes, greetings and quotes
Who is Karthik Naralasetty? Indian-American who could be Texas’s youngest mayor

description: A goods train carrying food grains derailed near MUPA in Assam's Maligaon, disrupting train services. The incident occurred inside tunnel number 2, and several trains have been canceled. Repair and restoration efforts are ongoing, with senior railway officials at the site. Normal operations are expected to resume shortly, according to Northeast Frontier Railway.
title: Goods train wagon derails in Assam's Maligaon, rail services disrupted
Israel arrests couple allegedly linked to Iran for spying on Mossad HQ

description: All ten IPL 2025 franchises revealed their retained players, with Kolkata Knight Riders and Rajasthan Royals utilizing their full quota, while Punjab Kings retained only two uncapped players. Punjab now have the largest auction budget of Rs 110.5 crore, whereas Rajasthan Royals will enter the auction with Rs 41 crore.

description: TPG Nambiar, founder of BPL, passed away at nearly 95. He was a pioneering innovator and industrialist who contributed significantly to India's electronics industry. Nambiar is survived by his family, who mourn his death. Prime minister Narendra Modi and other notable figures expressed their condolences, acknowledging his legacy and impact.

The National Conference echoed this sentiment, demanding a return to pre-August 2019 status. LG Manoj Sinha urged acceptance of the current Union territory status.
title: 'It's black day for us': Mehbooba Mufti has a message for J&K governor

description: Mumbai Indians have decided to retain five key players ahead of the upcoming IPL mega auction. Jasprit Bumrah has been named the top retained player, followed by Hardik Pandya, Suryakumar Yadav, Rohit Sharma, and Tilak Verma. Coach Mahela Jayawardene emphasizes playing for pride as they aim to rebuild.

description: The retained players list from all ten franchises of the Indian Premier League (IPL) has been released, marking a crucial step in the lead-up to the IPL 2025 mega auction scheduled for the last week of November.
title: IPL: Full list of players retained by their respective franchises

description: Hezbollah's new leader, Naim Qassem, signaled willingness for a ceasefire with Israel, demanding specific conditions. Negotiations include Israel's call for Hezbollah's withdrawal and Lebanese army deployment along the border. Lebanon and Israeli officials express cautious optimism, while US diplomatic efforts continue amid ongoing conflict in Lebanon and Gaza, generating significant casualties.
title: 'If they want to stop ...': New Hezbollah chief open to truce with Israel if offer is made
Air India cancels 60+ US flights amid peak season

description: Diwali 2024 Puja Muhurat: Lakshmi Puja, an essential ritual during Diwali, involves cleaning the home, setting up a sacred platform, positioning deities, and performing detailed offerings such as flowers, fruits, sweets, and mantras. The puja is conducted to invite Goddess Lakshmi for blessings of peace, wealth, and prosperity.

description: Sharad Pawar criticized Ajit Pawar and other NCP members for causing a split in the party for power, referring to their alliance with BJP and Shiv Sena. He expressed his disappointment with the defection, especially addressing minister Walse Patil, and urged support for Devdatta Nikam in the upcoming elections.

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi, celebrating Diwali with military personnel in Gujarat's Kutch region, lauded the dedication and strength of India's armed forces. Emphasizing a zero-tolerance approach to border compromise, he praised their critical role in ensuring national security and contributing to India's progress towards becoming a developed nation.
title: 'We trust determination of our soldiers, not words of our enemies': PM Modi

description: BR Naidu, newly appointed chairperson of the TTD board, aims to ensure all employees of the Tirumala Tirupati Devasthanam are Hindus. He plans discussions with the government on managing non-Hindu staff, suggesting transfers or retirements. Naidu also raised concerns about irregularities under the previous YSR Congress administration.
title: 'Everyone who works at Tirumala should be Hindu': TTD chief BR Naidu

description: Cyclone Dana caused heavy rains in Kolkata, making Chhatim trees shed their fragrant flowers. This event provided relief to those suffering from allergies and asthma. The flowers, known for their strong scent, were affecting residents' breathing. The shedding of flowers has helped ease the situation for sensitive individuals in affected areas.
title: Kolkata breaths easy as cyclone Dana clears allergy-inducing Chhatim flowers

description: Congress president Mallikarjun Kharge dismisses PM Narendra Modi's One Nation, One Election proposal as impossible due to the need for parliamentary consensus. Modi contends it will strengthen democracy and optimize resources. The opposition criticizes the plan as impractical and harmful to federalism.
title: 'One nation, one election impossible': Kharge reacts to PM Modi's remarks

description: At least 158 people have died in Spain following severe floods caused by torrential rains, the worst in nearly thirty years. Prime Minister Pedro Sánchez urged unity, declared three days of national mourning. Rescue operations continue with warnings to avoid flooded areas. Experts cite a meteorological phenomenon for the intense rainfall.
title: Spain's deadliest flooding in decades kills 158: Rainstorms ruin homes

description: Anand Mahindra, chairman of Mahindra Group, shared a heartfelt Diwali message on X, highlighting the festival's significance in symbolizing the victory of light over darkness and good over evil. His post has garnered significant attention, resonating with many users who shared their own Diwali wishes, expressing gratitude for Mahindra's inspiring message.
title: ‘That’s the Promise of Diwali…’: Read Anand Mahindra’s message of Diwali

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi celebrated Diwali with BSF, Army, Navy, and Air Force personnel in the challenging terrains of Sir Creek, Gujarat. Since 2014, Modi has made it a tradition to spend the festival with troops. He also honoured Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel on National Unity Day and extended Diwali greetings to the nation.
title: Watch: Continuing tradition, PM Modi spends Diwali with soldiers

description: A 54-year-old man, Chandrakant Patel, was arrested for raping and recording sexual assaults on four young girls aged 8 to 11 in Nadiad. Patel lured the girls with sweets and money before committing the crimes. Police found hundreds of obscene videos on his phone, and further action will follow after forensic analysis.
title: 'Hundreds of videos': Gujarat painter raped four girls, recorded act

description: As Team India gears up for the final Test against New Zealand, speculation arises over KL Rahul's potential inclusion. Balancing Rahul's experience against Washington Sundar's impressive comeback, the team's strategy will hinge on Mumbai's pitch. India's series loss adds pressure, as they aim to qualify for the ICC World Test Championship final.
title: 3rd Test: Bring KL Rahul in or not?

description: The White House military band performed "Om Jai Jagdish Hare" in a Diwali celebration at President Joe Biden's residence. Over 600 Indian Americans attended, including Congress members and corporate leaders. Biden lit a diya and praised the South Asian American community's contributions, highlighting the tradition's continuation since President George Bush's tenure in 2003.

description: Indian and Chinese troops exchanged sweets along the LAC on Diwali, following the recent disengagement in Demchok and Depsang Plains. This comes after extensive talks to de-escalate 2020 tensions. Defence Minister Rajnath Singh expressed optimism, and Chinese Ambassador Xu Feihong emphasized constructive conflict management. The engagement also saw a meeting between PM Modi and President Xi Jinping.

description: Indian head coach Gautam Gambhir emphasizes collective responsibility for the team's recent Test series defeat against New Zealand. Despite the setbacks, Gambhir believes the losses will motivate young players to improve. He stresses adapting to Test cricket conditions and highlights strong defense as crucial for player success across formats.

description: Defence minister Rajnath Singh announced nearing completion of disengagement efforts along the LAC in eastern Ladakh, with ongoing efforts for long-term peace with China. Recent dialogues fostered a consensus to restore the pre-standoff situation, focusing on mutual security, patrolling, and grazing rights. Singh also honored Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel's contributions.
title: 'Will strive to move beyond disengagement': Rajnath on India-China LAC pact

description: Mumbai's Muslim population, making up 20%, has few candidates in major parties' lists despite significant representation in some constituencies. Congress and NCP lead with the highest number of Muslim nominees. However, dissatisfaction looms over the MVA's minimal consideration. The situation might benefit smaller parties such as AIMIM and VBA in upcoming polls.
title: Maharashtra polls: Major parties nominate less than 10 Muslims in all across Mumbai

description: National security advisors Ajit Doval and Jake Sullivan held a telephonic discussion focusing on regional security and stability in the Indo-Pacific. They also highlighted advancements in the bilateral partnership, including technology initiatives and defense cooperation, in addition to coordinated patrolling in Eastern Ladakh following disengagement between India and China.
title: NSA Ajit Doval speaks to US counterpart Jake Sullivan on Indo-Pacific region stability

description: In Kakinada district, an elderly woman, Akasam Saraswathi, and her daughter Swati ended their lives. Saraswathi had severe health issues, and Swati, devoted to her care, stayed single. Police found Saraswathi's body on a bed and Swati hanging from a ceiling fan. A case is under investigation.

description: Ravi Raja, the former opposition leader in the BMC, has resigned from the Congress party after 44 years of service. He felt unrecognized despite his request for a ticket in the upcoming Maharashtra assembly elections. The Congress selected an inexperienced candidate for Sion Koliwada. Raja will be joining the BJP today.

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi, during his National Unity Day address, reiterated the importance of 'one nation, one election' and the implementation of a uniform civil code. He warned against divisive forces aiming to destabilize India and highlighted the country's progress towards unity, celebrating Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel's legacy and efforts in integrating princely states post-independence.

description: North Korea tested a new intercontinental ballistic missile under Kim Jong Un's orders, aiming to showcase its military power. Officials are concerned about North Korea's emerging solid-fueled missile technology and potential military involvement in the Ukraine conflict.
